My gripe with Mwendwa is his ill-advised move to declare journalists from certain media houses persona non grata at football match venues.On this score, he has bitten more than he can chew. There was a time when the powers that be in Kenyan football treated journalists like lap dogs, adorable ‘pets’ at the beck and call of then federation boss, Sam Nyamweya.
Nyamweya, a man who is 'generous' to a fault, would liberally dish out pocket change to scribes at every press conference he called.



